review_blob:
This is my go to PA.
Its readily available at corner stores in 24oz bottles.
This is the lowest I go on the todem pole.
An amber pour with a flowery scent. 
Slight hops mixed well with the barley.
Its one of those common goes down smooth brews.
This is a drinking at a bbq during the day beer.

Definitely a little thin.
This is a good everyday IPA.
A go to in a tight spot.
Cheers.
